property.name: id
property.shortdesc: The unique ID of the CellStyle.

property.name: isValid
property.shortdesc: Returns true if the object specifier resolves to valid objects.

property.name: parent
property.shortdesc: The parent of the CellStyle (a Document, Application or CellStyleGroup).

property.name: index
property.shortdesc: The index of the CellStyle within its containing object.

property.name: events
property.shortdesc: A collection of events.

property.name: eventListeners
property.shortdesc: A collection of event listeners.

property.name: basedOn
property.shortdesc: The style that this style is based on. Can return: CellStyle or String.

property.name: appliedParagraphStyle
property.shortdesc: The paragraph style applied to the text. Can return: ParagraphStyle or NothingEnum enumerator. Can also accept: String.

property.name: gradientFillLength
property.shortdesc: The length (of a linear gradient) or radius (of a radial gradient) applied to the fill of the object. Can return: Real or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: gradientFillAngle
property.shortdesc: The angle of a linear gradient applied to the fill of the object. (Range: -180 to 180). Can return: Real or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: gradientFillStart
property.shortdesc: The starting point (in page coordinates) of a gradient applied to the fill of the CellStyle, in the format [x, y]. Can return: Array of 2 Units or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: topInset
property.shortdesc: The top inset of the cell. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: leftInset
property.shortdesc: The left inset of the cell. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: bottomInset
property.shortdesc: The bottom inset of the cell. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: rightInset
property.shortdesc: The right inset of the cell. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: fillColor
property.shortdesc: The swatch (color, gradient, tint, or mixed ink) applied to the fill of the object. Can return: Swatch or NothingEnum enumerator. Can also accept: String.

property.name: fillTint
property.shortdesc: The tint (as a percentage) of the fill of the object. Can return: Real or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: overprintFill
property.shortdesc: If true, the fill of the object will overprint. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: topLeftDiagonalLine
property.shortdesc: If true, draws a diagonal line starting from the top left. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: topRightDiagonalLine
property.shortdesc: If true, draws a diagonal line starting from the top right. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: diagonalLineInFront
property.shortdesc: If true, draws the diagonal line in front of cell contents. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: diagonalLineStrokeWeight
property.shortdesc: The diagonal line stroke weight. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: diagonalLineStrokeType
property.shortdesc: The stroke type of the diagonal line(s). Can return: StrokeStyle or NothingEnum enumerator. Can also accept: String.

property.name: diagonalLineStrokeColor
property.shortdesc: The diagonal line color, specified as a swatch. Can return: Swatch or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: diagonalLineStrokeTint
property.shortdesc: The diagonal line tint (as a percentage). (Range: 0 to 100). Can return: Real or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: diagonalLineStrokeOverprint
property.shortdesc: If true, the diagonal line stroke will overprint. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: diagonalLineStrokeGapColor
property.shortdesc: The swatch (color, gradient, tint, or mixed ink) applied to the gap of the diagonal line stroke. Note: Not valid when diagonal line stroke type is solid. Can return: Swatch or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: diagonalLineStrokeGapTint
property.shortdesc: The tint (as a percentage) of the diagonal line stroke gap color. Note: Not valid when diagonal line stroke type is solid. Can return: Real or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: diagonalLineStrokeGapOverprint
property.shortdesc: If true, the stroke gap of the diagonal line will overprint. Note: Not valid when diagonal line stroke type is solid. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: clipContentToCell
property.shortdesc: If true, clips the cell's content to width and height of the cell. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: firstBaselineOffset
property.shortdesc: The distance between the baseline of the text and the top inset of the cell. Can return: FirstBaseline enumerator or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: verticalJustification
property.shortdesc: The vertical alignment of cell. Can return: VerticalJustification enumerator or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: paragraphSpacingLimit
property.shortdesc: The maximum space that can be added between paragraphs in a cell. Note: Valid only when vertical justification is justified. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: minimumFirstBaselineOffset
property.shortdesc: The space between the baseline of the text and the top inset of the frame or cell. Can return: Unit (0 - 8640 points) or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: rotationAngle
property.shortdesc: The rotation angle (in degrees) of the cell, specified as one of the following values: 0, 90, 180, or 270. Can return: Real or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: leftEdgeStrokeWeight
property.shortdesc: The stroke weight of the left edge border stroke. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: leftEdgeStrokeType
property.shortdesc: The stroke type of the left edge. Can return: StrokeStyle or NothingEnum enumerator. Can also accept: String.

property.name: leftEdgeStrokeColor
property.shortdesc: The swatch (color, gradient, tint, or mixed ink) applied to the left edge border stroke. Can return: Swatch or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: leftEdgeStrokeTint
property.shortdesc: The tint (as a percentage) of the left edge border stroke. (Range: 0 to 100). Can return: Real or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: leftEdgeStrokeOverprint
property.shortdesc: If true, the left edge border stroke will overprint. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: leftEdgeStrokeGapColor
property.shortdesc: The swatch (color, gradient, tint, or mixed ink) applied to the gap of the left edge border stroke. Note: Not valid when left edge stroke type is solid. Can return: Swatch or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: leftEdgeStrokeGapTint
property.shortdesc: The tint (as a percentage) of the left edge border stroke gap color. (Range: 0 to 100) Note: Not valid when left edge stroke type is solid. Can return: Real or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: leftEdgeStrokeGapOverprint

property.name: topEdgeStrokeGapTint
property.shortdesc: The tint (as a percentage) of the top edge border stroke gap color. (Range: 0 to 100) Note: Not valid when top edge stroke type is solid. Can return: Real or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: topEdgeStrokeGapOverprint
property.shortdesc: If true, the gap color of the top edge border stroke will overprint. Note: Not valid when top edge stroke type is solid. . Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: rightEdgeStrokeWeight
property.shortdesc: The stroke weight of the right edge border stroke. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: rightEdgeStrokeType
property.shortdesc: The stroke type of the right edge. Can return: StrokeStyle or NothingEnum enumerator. Can also accept: String.

property.name: rightEdgeStrokeColor
property.shortdesc: The color, specified as a swatch, of the right edge border stroke. Can return: Swatch or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.shortdesc: If true, the gap color of the right edge border stroke will overprint. Note: Not valid when right edge stroke type is solid. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: name
property.shortdesc: The name of the style.

property.name: label
property.shortdesc: A property that can be set to any string.

property.name: properties
property.shortdesc: A property that allows setting of several properties at the same time.

parameters.name: replacingWith
parameters.shortdesc: The style to apply in place of the deleted style.

method.name: move
method.shortdesc: Moves the style to the specified location.

parameters.name: to
parameters.shortdesc: The location relative to the reference object or within the containing object.

parameters.name: reference
parameters.shortdesc: The reference object. Note: Required when the to parameter specifies before or after. Can accept: ParagraphStyle, ParagraphStyleGroup, CharacterStyle, CharacterStyleGroup, CellStyle, CellStyleGroup, TableStyle, TableStyleGroup, Document or Application.

method.name: insertLabel
method.shortdesc: Sets the label to the value associated with the specified key.

method.name: extractLabel
method.shortdesc: Gets the label value associated with the specified key.

method.name: toSource
method.shortdesc: Generates a string which, if executed, will return the CellStyle.

method.name: getElements
method.shortdesc: Resolves the object specifier, creating an array of object references.

parameters.name: handler
parameters.shortdesc: The event handler. Can accept: File or JavaScript Function.

parameters.name: handler
parameters.shortdesc: The registered event handler. Can accept: File or JavaScript Function.
